  [8] I think part of the case against short-sale bans is that this isn=E2=
=80=99t really true, and that a short-sale ban can *depress* bank stocks by=
 creating an overhang that makes them uninvestable. If there=E2=80=99s a 14=
-day ban on shorting bank stocks, you might assume =E2=80=9Cwell on day 15 =
everyone=E2=80=99s gonna short these bank stocks, so why would I buy them n=
ow?=E2=80=9D And so you wait, and nobody buys them and they go down.=20


  [9] I did not *love* it as a way to deter political advocacy, but that is=
 not relevant to our current story.


  [10] Dave Guarino on Twitter  pointed me to this exchange, and asked me t=
o, you know, make fun of it for being securities fraud.


